    • Method Detail

      • read

        public Envelope read(InputStream inputStream)
              throws InvalidEnvelopeException
        Parses an InputStream to produce an Envelope.
        Parameters:
        inputStream - an InputStream that contains a valid/parsable Envelope. This InputStream will be closed after reading.
        Returns:
        An instance of Envelope based on the data from InputStream. Does not verify the envelope/signature(s).
        Throws:
        InvalidEnvelopeException - when the InputStream does not contain a parsable Envelope.
        EnvelopeReadingException - when there were issues parsing some elements of the Envelope. The parsed envelope and all encountered exceptions can be retrieved from this exception.

      • create

        public Envelope create(List<Document> files,
                       List<Annotation> annotations)
                throws InvalidEnvelopeException,
                       SignatureException
        Creates a Envelope with the input documents and annotations and a signature covering them.
        Parameters:
        files - list of Document to be added and signed; can NOT be null.
        annotations - list of Annotation to be added and signed; can be null.
        Returns:
        A new Envelope which contains the documents and annotations and a signature covering them.
        Throws:
        InvalidEnvelopeException - when composing the Envelope fails or its verification fails.
        SignatureException - when acquiring root signature from signing service fails.

      • addSignature

        public Envelope addSignature(Envelope existingEnvelope,
                             List<Document> files,
                             List<Annotation> annotations)
                      throws InvalidEnvelopeException,
                             EnvelopeMergingException,
                             SignatureException
        Creates a SignatureContent that contains the new set of documents, annotations and a signature for the added elements and adds it to the SignatureContent copied from existing Envelope before composing the new Envelope.
        Parameters:
        existingEnvelope - an instance of Envelope which already has EnvelopeSignature(s).
        files - list of Document to be added and signed; can NOT be null.
        annotations - list of Annotation to be added and signed; can be null.
        Returns:
        A new instance of Envelope that contains copied content of existingEnvelope and the newly signed SignatureContent.
        Throws:
        InvalidEnvelopeException - when composing the Envelope fails or its verification fails.
        EnvelopeMergingException - when there are issues adding the newly created SignatureContent to existingEnvelope.
        SignatureException - when acquiring root signature from signing service fails.
